OL,6,F"Will he make plain that in the event
OL,7,Fthey try and manoeuvre us into a
OL,8,Fnationalisation we'll pay not more
OL,9,Fthan a penny for it?"
OL,11,FMr Reynolds replied: "To be clear, we
OL,12,Fwould always in a situation where the
OL,13,Fstate transfers a change of ownership
OL,14,Fto it pay the fair market value for
OL,15,Fthose assets. In this case the market
OL,16,Fvalue is effectively zero so I take
OL,17,Fhis point entirely.
